The paper discusses training a network to generate mappings between training sets and classification policies, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of attentional mechanisms and optimization for performance in low-data and unsupervised learning regimes suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of small datasets and classification tasks suggests a potential focus on computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the use of neural networks for generating classifiers suggests a potential focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
